			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2016</a> paper:</span><br><i>BSML-mbeddr: Integrating Semantically Configurable State-Machine Models in a C Programming Environment</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/ZhaoyiLuo.html">Zhaoyi Luo</a>, <a href="../profile/JoanneMAtlee.html">Joanne M. Atlee</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/2997364.2997372">10.1145/2997364.2997372</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1d.html"><span class="tagM">T1D: Composition</span></a><ul><li> It integrates state-machine DSMLs into a C programming environment (mbeddr), focusing on embedding/composition.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3c.html"><span class="tagL">T3C: DSLs</span></a><ul><li> BSML is a family of domain-specific modeling languages for executable state machines.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1c.html"><span class="tagL">T1C: Behavioural Semantics</span></a><ul><li> The work concerns executable semantics for state-machine models.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4c.html"><span class="tagL">T4C: Vertical Transformation</span></a><ul><li> It connects high-level models to executable C-level artifacts via generation/compilation in the environment.
</li></ul></li></ul>
